Hello again-

The story got picked up in the mainstream press today, this time in the
Daily Telegraph, the UK's largest newspaper (according to wikipedia).

http://tinyurl.com/alifeDailyTele

This time they added a picture of the Terminator!

Note the comment at the bottom claiming that HyperNEAT technology is nothing
new (e.g., vs. RBFs), from someone who knows about evolutionary computation
and neural nets. If you feel like it, jump on and make a comment about why
you think HyperNEAT represents something interesting and novel.


Best regards,
Jeff Clune
